    <section xml:id="installation">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <subtitle>Docker based Quick Installation Guide</subtitle>            
        <section xml:id="prerequisites">
            <title>Prerequisites</title>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        Docker ( 
                            <link xlink:href="https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/" xlink:show="new">Docker Desktop</link>, 
                            <link xlink:href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/install" xlink:show="new">Docker Engine</link> or
                            <link xlink:href="https://podman.io/docs/installation" xlink:show="new">Podman</link>
                        )
                    </para>                    
                </listitem>
                <listitem><para>A modern web browser</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <para> When using the Docker image, you do <emphasis role="bold">not</emphasis> need
                    <link xlink:href="https://www.java.com/" xlink:show="new">Java</link> or <link
                    xlink:href="https://exist-db.org/" xlink:show="new">eXist-db</link> installed
                locally. If you do <emphasis role="bold">not</emphasis> want to use the Docker
                continue with <link xlink:href="installation.xml?id=exist-installation">installing
                    into an eXist instance</link>. Find more information on TEI Publisher and Docker
                    <link xlink:href="installation.xml?id=docker">here</link>. </para>
        </section>
        <section xml:id="running">
            <title>Running TEI Publisher</title>
            <para>Make sure Docker is running and start TEI Publisher using the official pre-built
                Docker image by running the following command from your terminal: </para>
            <para>
            <programlisting>docker run -p 8080:8080 -v exist-data:/exist/data
                existdb/teipublisher:latest</programlisting>
            </para>
            <para>Point your browser to <link
                    xlink:href="http://localhost:8080/exist/apps/tei-publisher/doc/tldr.xml" xlink:show="new"
                    >localhost:8080/exist/apps/tei-publisher/doc/tldr.xml</link> to verify everthing
                works fine. You should see this page but now served by the TEI Publisher Docker
                Container you just started.</para>
            <para><emphasis role="bold"><important>Please be aware that the TEI Publisher Dev Docker image is not hardened!</important></emphasis></para>
            <para>To run TEI Publisher on the internet please make sure to read <link
                    xlink:href="tldr.xml#production">Running TEI Publisher in Production</link> below.</para>
            
            <para>The default landing page of the Docker image is <link
                    xlink:href="/"
                    >localhost:8080</link> and it was built from a
                    <link xlink:href="quickstart.xml?id=intro-jinks#intro-jinks">Jinks
                    profile</link>. Jinks is the new TEI Publisher application manager. The <link
                        xlink:href="/" xlink:show="new">TEI Publisher homepage</link> consists of three different <emphasis
                    role="bold">Jinks profiles</emphasis> and Jinks itself:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem><link xlink:href="/exist/apps/tei-publisher/browse.html" xlink:show="new">Documentation &amp; Demo </link> - this article is part of the profile for self-guided learning.</listitem>
                <listitem><link xlink:href="/exist/apps/tp-serafin/" xlink:show="new">Serafin</link>- Real-world correspondence edition example</listitem>
                <listitem><link xlink:href="/exist/apps/tp-annotator/">Workbench</link> - Interactive TEI editing</listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <para>Via the <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/dashboard" xlink:show="new">eXist-db Dashboard</link> you can see all installed Jinks profiles and further
                installed eXist-db applications and the TEI Publisher application manager <link xlink:href="/exist/apps/jinks" xlink:show="new">Jinks</link> itself.</para>
        </section>
    </section>
