    <section xml:id="production">
        <title>TEI Publisher in Production Environments</title>
        <para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="bold"><important>Make sure TEI Publisher runs on a hardened eXist-db.</important></emphasis></para>
                    <para>Either use these hardened eXist-db images like <link
                            xlink:href="https://hub.docker.com/layers/duncdrum/existdb/release-nonroot-slim/images/sha256-0957a844af0a9d4b1b246c361956d9f13985b7b4b66e0ebc27736f14eacc2eab" xlink:show="new"
                            >duncdrum/existdb:release-nonroot-slim</link> in a Docker Compose setup,
                        create your own images or install <link
                            xlink:href="http://exist-db.org/exist/apps/doc/basic-installation" xlink:show="new">eXist-db
                            bare metal</link>. In any case please make sure to read the eXist-db
                        Documentation on "<link
                            xlink:href="http://exist-db.org/exist/apps/doc/production_good_practice" xlink:show="new"
                            >Production Use - Good Practice</link>".</para></listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para><emphasis role="bold"><important>It is strongly recommended to use a <link
                                    xlink:href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Proxy_server" xlink:show="new">proxy server
                    </link>in production environments!</important></emphasis></para>
                    <para>See <link
                            xlink:href="documentation.xml?id=proxy">running behind a
                            proxy</link>.</para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem><link xlink:href="https://www.e-editiones.org/pages/get-in-touch/" xlink:show="new">Get in
                        touch</link> in case you or your IT Department are having any security concerns
                    about hosting TEI Publisher. If self hosting is not an option see <link
                        xlink:href="documentation.xml?id=hosting" xlink:show="new">Hosting
                        Options</link>.</listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
    </section>    
